he '''European qualification''' for the '''[[2015 World Men's Handball Championship]]''', in [[Qatar]], was disputed in two rounds among the teams that did not qualify for the [[2014 European Men's Handball Championship]] and the 12 teams that placed outside of the European Championship's top three (excluding [[Spain national handball team|Spain]], which were qualified automatically for the World Championship as holders).\n\nIn the first round of qualification, 20 teams not participating at the European Championship were split into five groups; the group winners advanced to the second round, joining the 12 European finalists and [[Germany national handball team|Germany]], which was given a [[bye (sports)|bye]] to this round. These 18 teams then were paired to play a two-legged playoff tie to determine the nine remaining World Championship qualifiers from Europe.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurohandball.com/article/017302/Procedure+for+2015+World+Championship+Qualification+Europe|title=Procedure for 2015 World Championship Qualification Europe approved|date=2013-06-21|work=eurohandball.com|accessdate=2013-06-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurohandball.com/article/017308/Draw+procedure+for+first+phase+of+2015+World+Championship+Qualification+Europe+released|title=Draw procedure for first phase of 2015 World Championship Qualification Europe released|date=2013-06-24|work=eurohandball.com|accessdate=2013-06-24}}</ref>\n\n==Group stage==\nThe draw was held on 27 June 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurohandball.com/article/17333|title=20 teams vie for a spot at 2015 World Championship Play-Offs Europe|date=2013-06-27|work=eurohandball.com|accessdate=2013-06-27}}</ref> The group winners advanced to the playoff round.\n\n===Group 1===\n{{Handball table start}}\n{{hbt-row |team={{hb|LTU}} |bg=a |w=4 |d=1 |l=1 |gf=145 |ga=132}}\n{{hbt-row |team={{hb|GEO}} |bg= |w=3 |d=0 |l=3 |gf=149 |ga=156}}\n{{hbt-row |team={{hb|FIN}} |bg= |w=2 |d=1 |l=3 |gf=143 |ga=139}}\n